                <head>46. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 5, 1970, signing ceremonies for the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty
                    were held in Moscow and Washington, D.C. For text of President <persName
                        corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>’s remarks on the occasion, made after
                    signing the proclamation of the treaty at the Department of State, see <hi
                        rend="italic">Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States:
                            <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Richard Nixon</persName>, 1970</hi>, pages
                    241–242. For the text of the treaty, see 21 UST 483.</p>
            </div>
